Diving into macOS tools . Here's a guide to key features and commands for efficient computing.

macOS File Types & App Store:
.dmg (Disk Image, mountable).
.pkg (Installer Package).
.app (Application bundle).
App Store: Centralized updates/patches; automatic or manual.
Uninstallation: Drag .app to Trash.

Apple ID & Backups:
---Personal Apple ID for data/purchases; corporate uses Managed IDs with MDM.
---Time Machine: Hourly/daily/weekly backups; deletes oldest when full.

Anti-Virus & System Preferences:
---No built-in AV; use 3rd-party.
System Preferences: Like Control Panel‚Äîdisplays, network, printers, privacy, accessibility.

macOS Features:
--Mission Control/Spaces: View/manage desktops.
--Keychain: Encrypted password manager.
--Spotlight: Search files/apps (Command-Space).
--iCloud: Cross-device sharing/backups.
--Gestures: Trackpad swipes/pinches.
--Finder: File manager; remote disc sharing.
--Dock: App launcher; auto-hide option.
--Disk Utility: Manage disks/images; verify/repair.
--FileVault: Full disk encryption.
--Terminal: Command-line access.
--Force Quit: Stop apps (Command-Option-Escape).


